QUE- How does request reaches application which is created as pod in kubernates cluster , when user send request ?
ANS-The standard end-to-end flow involves DNS --> Cloud/External Load Balancer --> Ingress Controller --> Kubernetes Service --> Pod.

1. DNS Resolution (The Entry Point)
The user types a URL (e.g., [https://myapp.example.com](https://myapp.example.com)) into their browser.

A DNS lookup translates that domain name into a public IP address. This IP address belongs to your cloud provider's load balancer or the cluster's edge gateway.

5. kube-proxy & Node Routing (The Network Layer)Every node in a Kubernetes cluster runs a daemon called kube-proxy. 
 kube-proxy maintains network rules (using Linux iptables or IPVS) on the node. When the Service intercepts traffic, these rules intercept the 
 packet and route it across the cluster network to the specific IP address of the chosen target Pod.

