QUE - devloper accidentally push some sensitive information that access key and secret key to the git hub ,
As a devops engineer what are actions need to take immediately to prevent this ?

ANS-  Deactivate/Delete the Compromised Keys:

Go immediately to your cloud provider console (e.g., AWS IAM Console).

Deactivate or Delete the specific Access Key ID that was leaked. This instantly cuts off any unauthorized actor using those credentials.

Generate New Credentials:

Create a fresh set of access keys for your applications or services.

Update your secure storage (CI/CD secrets manager, HashiCorp Vault, etc.) with the new keys.

To prevent this we are maintaining secrete key & information in aws secret manager or hashi corp value .

